{"id":25338,"date":"2017-10-25T15:02:26","date_gmt":"2017-10-25T11:02:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25338"},"modified":"2019-05-24T17:01:22","modified_gmt":"2019-05-24T13:01:22","slug":"ibn-qayyim-reason-nature","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/25\/ibn-qayyim-reason-nature\/","title":{"rendered":"Ibn Qayyim on Reason: Islam conforms to reason and nature"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn al-Qayyim reported: It was said to one of the Bedouins who embraced Islam, when he recognized the call of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, \u201cWhat made you become a Muslim? What did you see in him that told you he is the Messenger of Allah?\u201d The Bedouin said, \u201cThe Prophet did not command anything that my reason said should be prohibited. He did not prohibit anything that my reason said should be commanded. He did not allow anything that my reason said should be forbidden. And he did not forbid anything that my reason said should be allowed.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Ibn al-Qayyim said, \u201cLook at this Bedouin, his sound mind and his instincts, the strength of his faith, and his conclusion that the authenticity of the Prophet\u2019s call is due to its correspondence with everything the mind knows is good.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Mada\u0304rij al-Sa\u0304liki\u0304n 1\/250<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u064a\u0645 \u0642\u0650\u064a\u0644\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0628\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0636\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0642\u064e\u062f\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0641\u064e \u062f\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0648\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u064